          "lang": "en",
          "value": "The data collected included age, sex, body mass index (BMI = weight/height2, in kg/m2) and two speed criteria (m/s) measured 13. The categorisation of BMI for children was based on the French corpulence curves included in the National Health Nutrition Plan and the thresholds of the International Obesity Task Force (IOTF) 16 with the IOTF25 and IOTF30 criteria defining overweight and obesity. Children with a BMI below the 3rd percentile were considered underweight."
